        "description": "Following up from [this mailing list conversation|https://lists.apache.org/thread/nxncph842h8tyovxp04hrzq4y35lq4xq], I am wondering if the R package should rename `read_ipc_file()` / write_ipc_file()` to `read_arrow_file()`/ `write_arrow_file()`, or add an additional alias for both. It might also be helpful to update the documentation so that users read \"Write an Arrow file (formerly known as a Feather file)\" rather than the current Feather-named first approach, assuming there is a community decision to coalesce around the name Arrow for the file format, and the project is moving on from the name Feather.",
