                        "displayName": "Stephanie Hazlitt",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "The other {{{}arrow::read_*(){}}}functions don't use the {{_file}} in the name, just {{{}read_ipc_file(){}}}, which I am guessing is because we also have {{{}read_ipc_stream(){}}}. I wonder if {{read_arrow}} and {{read_arrow_stream}} would work and be more consistent with the naming API?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stephhazlitt",
                        "name": "stephhazlitt",
                        "key": "stephhazlitt",
                        "avatarUrls": {
